cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents an architecture for autonomous navigation of vehicles. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the decision-making and motion planning components of the proposed architecture. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper focuses on cooperative driving and platooning of multiple vehicles. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the decision-making component of the proposed architecture involves real-time information processing and selection of desired platoon configurations. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of perceptual knowledge sharing among connected vehicles.
